12/08/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met on Monday (11 August) with his Turkish and Italian counterparts, Recep Tayyip Erdogan and Silvio Berlusconi. Nano went to Istanbul to discuss prospects and developments in Albania's efforts for EU integration. During the meeting, Berlusconi confirmed Italy's support for Albania's EU bid. Italy holds the rotating EU presidency through the end of the year. Erdogan also pledged Turkish support -- both political and economic -- and said he would work to increase investment in Albania's strategic sectors, including infrastructure, telecommunications, tourism, power generation and distribution. (ATA, Anadolu Agency - 11/08/03)
